    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1866-12-06T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1866-12-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="189"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d189">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Sir F.
                        Bruce</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic"
                                >Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1866-12-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">December</hi> 6, 1866</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Sir:</hi> I have not yet received the transcripts
                    of the records of the late capital trials which have taken place in Canada. It
                    can well be conceived that the papers are voluminous, and the delay is,
                    therefore, unavoidable; nevertheless the 13th of December is near at hand. I beg
                    leave, therefore, to ask if you have it in your power to inform me of the
                    probable disposition of those cases.</p>
                <p>I am, my dear sir, very respectfully, yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Hon. Sir <hi rend="smallcaps">Frederick W. A. Bruce</hi>, &amp;<hi
                            rend="italic">c</hi>., &amp;<hi rend="italic">c</hi>., &amp;<hi
                            rend="italic">c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
